}} 'Innsbruck' is the capital city of the federal state of Tyrol (Tirol) in
western Austria. It is located in the Inn Valley at the junction with the
Wipptal (Sill River), which provides access to the Brenner Pass, some south of
Innsbruck. It is about half way between Munich (Germany) and Verona (Italy).
Located in the broad valley between high mountains, the Nordkette (Hafelekar, )
in the north, Patscherkofel () and Serles () in the south. It is an
internationally renowned winter sports centre, and hosted the 1964 and 1976
Winter Olympics as well as the 1984 and 1988 Winter Paralympics. Innsbruck
hosted the first Winter Youth Olympics in 2012. The word bruck comes from the
German word BrÃ¼cke meaning "bridge" which leads to "the bridge over the Inn".
